-- 
CDC, Others to Invest $1 Billion in Russian Ski Resorts Project

-- B y   V i d y a   R o o t
-- 
2011-09-16T09:56:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/cdc-others-to-invest-1-billion-in-russian-ski-resorts-project.html
French and international investors,
led by Caisse des Depots et Consignations, plan to invest about
$1 billion in the development of five ski resorts in the Russian
North Caucasus, a spokesman for the state-owned bank said.  The amount is a target for the investors, the spokesman
said, declining to be identified in line with the policies of
the bank. The total financing for the project is about $14
billion, he said.  Moscow-based Kommersant newspaper reported that an
agreement on the resorts may be signed today at the Sochi
Economic Forum in southern  Russia .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vidya Root in Paris at 
